{"lemma":"رَبَضِ","slug":"رَبَضِ","root":"ر.ب.ض","root_slug":"ر-ب-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14485","","n14487","n14488","n14489","n14490","n14491"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lie down, to squat (said of animals)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lurk, to be in position"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to park, to anchor"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put to lie down"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wife"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outskirts, precincts, suburb"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"place where animals lie down or lurk"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew רבץ (raváts)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14485","headword_ar":"رَبَضَ","root":"rbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuwDN","text_ar":"رُبُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboDN","text_ar":"رَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboDapN","text_ar":"رَبْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [the last an inf. n. of un.,] said of the sheep and goat, (S, A, Mgh, K,) and of the gazelle, (S, A,) and of the ox-kind, and the horse, (S,) or beast, (Msb,) and of the dog, (S, A,) [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lay down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid himself down, upon his breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraka","text_ar":"بَرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a camel, (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"javama","text_ar":"جَثَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a bird, (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasa","text_ar":"جَلَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man. (Mgh.) Said of a man, it means [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lay down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sat upon his knees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it may also mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sat upon his thighs and his buttocks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 172.) [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained fixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stationary, like an animal lying upon its breast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is shown by what here follows: whence a signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~aDa","text_ar":"رَبَّضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.] The saying of Mohammad to Ed- Dahhák, when he sent him to his people,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA","text_ar":"اـِذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotahumo faA@robiDo fiY daArihimo ZaboyFA","text_ar":"اَتَيْتَهُمْ فَا@رْبِضْ فِى دَارِهِمْ ظَبْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When thou comest to them, remain in their abode in security,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without fear, like the gazelle"},{"kind":"text","text":"in his covert: (IAar, ISd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trust them not, but be vigilant, like a wild animal, ready to spring up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for thou wilt be in the midst of the unbelievers; (Az, ISd, K; *) so, if anything induce in thee suspicion, thou mayest flee from them like the gazelle: (Az, ISd, TA:) accord. to each interpretation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZbyA","text_ar":"ظبيا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the accus. case as a denotative of state; the subst. being put in the place of the act. part. n., as though for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataZab~iyFA","text_ar":"مَتَظَبِّيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former of the two explanations is said to be the more agreeable with the circumstances of the case. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa AlA^asadu EalaY fariysatihi","text_ar":"رَبَضَ الاَسَدُ عَلَى فَرِيسَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqironu EalaY","text_ar":"القِرْنُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qironihi","text_ar":"قِرْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion laid himself down upon his breast"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraka","text_ar":"بَرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on his prey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the adversary on his adversary."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a beast)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodged, and abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a place. (TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became heavy, and slept, stretched upon the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa Eani Alganami","text_ar":"رَبَضَ عَنِ الغَنَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuwDN","text_ar":"رُبُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a ram)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstained from tupping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covering the ewes, and avoided it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being fatigued:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was unable to cover them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) one does not say, of a ram,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jafara","text_ar":"جَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) You say also of a ewe when she is pregnant,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado rubiDa EanohaA","text_ar":"قَدْ رُبِضَ عَنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn- 'Abbád, A.) And you say of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa Eano maEaAliY AlA^umuwri","text_ar":"رَبَضَ عَنْ مَعَالِى الاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abstained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held back, from seeking the means of acquiring eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDa","text_ar":"رَبَضَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayolu","text_ar":"اللَّيْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night cast its darkness"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"(expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY bnafosihi","text_ar":"اَلْقَى بنَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDahu","text_ar":"رَبَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, O, K,) but the latter aor. was afterwards rejected by IAar, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He betook himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repaired, to him for lodging, covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDatohu","text_ar":"رَبَضَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", and IAar is related to have said"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, but afterwards to have retracted it, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a wife, or sister, or other woman,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertook,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"managed, his affairs, and gave him lodging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she was to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though she were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaD","text_ar":"رَبَض"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abawotuhu","text_ar":"اَبَوْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ I was to him a father, ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amamotuhu","text_ar":"اَمَمْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ I was to him a mother. ” (A, TA.) [The aor. occurs in the K, in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobiDu zawojahaA","text_ar":"تَرْبِضُ زَوْجَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the TA:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1012},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turab~iDu","text_ar":"تُرَبِّضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the L,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobuDu","text_ar":"تَرْبُضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus also the aor. is written in a copy of the A.]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","Mgh","TA","IAar","ISd","Az","O"]},{"entry_id":"n14487","headword_ar":"رَبْضٌ","root":"rbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14488","headword_ar":"رُبْضٌ","root":"rbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places. ―         -b2-  Also, accord. to Ks, (S,) and As, (Sgh, TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (S, Sgh, K:) but this is disapproved by Sh. (T, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A collection of trees of the kinds called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloH","text_ar":"طَلْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samur","text_ar":"سَمُر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection of abundant and dense trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Sgh","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n14489","headword_ar":"رِبْضٌ","root":"rbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyDN","text_ar":"رَبِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14490","headword_ar":"رَبَضٌ","root":"rbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodging-place"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sheep or goats; (S, A, * K;) because they lie therein upon their breasts; and in like manner of wild animals: (TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nightly lodging-place"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sheep or goats: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marobiDN","text_ar":"مَرْبِضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (S, * A, Mgh, Msb:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaADN","text_ar":"اَرْبَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, * TA:) and of the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAbiDu","text_ar":"مَرَابِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K: *) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrAbD","text_ar":"مرابض"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sheep or goats are like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaATin","text_ar":"مَعَاطِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels. (S.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of abode: a place of abode"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) pl. as above. (A.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything to which a man betakes himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repairs, for lodging, covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, A, * Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and at which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which, he finds rest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as a house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, A, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, A, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of subsistence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and hence, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk which sustains a man, and suffices him for food:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K: *) pl. as above: (K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboDN","text_ar":"رَبْضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboDN","text_ar":"رُبْضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Sgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuDN","text_ar":"رُبُضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) are applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wife"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^an~ahaA tarobiDu zawojahaA","text_ar":"لِاَنَّهَا تَرْبِضُ زَوْجَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in copies of the K and in the TA, but in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turab~iDu","text_ar":"تُرَبِّضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) i. e. because she undertakes, or manages, the affairs of her husband, and gives him lodging, or refuge; (TA;) or because she fixes him, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turab~iDuhu","text_ar":"تُرَبِّضُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuvab~ituhu","text_ar":"تُثَبِّتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) so that he does not quit his place: (L, TA:) or to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sister;"},{"kind":"text","text":"who undertakes, or manages, the affairs of ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuEaz~ibu","text_ar":"تُعَزِّبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in copies of the K and in the TA, in the latter of which it is thus explained, but in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuqar~ibu","text_ar":"تُقَرِّبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) her relation. (K.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"jaA='a Al$~itaA='u walam~aA A^at~axi*o rabaDFA\n                      \n                     \n                        yaA wayoHa kaf~aY~a mino Hafori AlqaraAmiySi"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The winter has come, and I have not yet made for myself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lodging:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O, wo to my two-hands, in consequence of digging"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hollows in which to sit for protection from the cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to “ milk which sustains a man, and suffices him for food, ” originated the prov., (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka rabaDuka waA_ino kaAna","text_ar":"مِنْكَ رَبَضُكَ وَاـِنْ كَانَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaArFA","text_ar":"سَمَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy family and thy servants"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and those to whom thou betakest thyself for lodging or refuge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are appertenances of thine, though they be persons falling short"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of their duty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy manager of affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though he be not a good manager of thine affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any woman who undertakes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manages, the affairs of a house"},{"kind":"text","text":": but in the T we find ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboDuka","text_ar":"رُبْضُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus written, as by Th, on the authority of IAar, but not restricted by a measure, and explained as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the person who undertakes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manages, the affairs of thy house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so in the book of proverbs by As: and in the margin"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a copy of"},{"kind":"text","text":"the S, we find the above-cited prov. thus written,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_ino kaAna samaArFA","text_ar":"وَاـِنْ كَانَ سَمَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka rubuDuka","text_ar":"مِنْكَ رُبُضُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as from the “ Book on Goats ” by Ibn-Zeyd, and expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sons of thy father are appertenances of thine, though they be evil persons, in whom is no good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wall"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a city: (K, TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"environs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a city, (S, A, Mgh,) and of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSor","text_ar":"قَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or palace &c.], (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of houses"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwellings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of open country:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboDN","text_ar":"رُبْضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (TA:) or this latter signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foundation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basis, of a building;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a city"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: (K:) IKh writes it ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuDN","text_ar":"رُبُضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and some say that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboDN","text_ar":"رُبْضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same: (TA:) the former of these two signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that touches the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) so says Sh: accord. to ISh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruboDu","text_ar":"رُبْضُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what touches the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lateral,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an outward"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjacent, part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lateral,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outward"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjacent, parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (Ks, S:) also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space immediately pertaining to a mosque:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaADN","text_ar":"اَرْبَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained by El-Karkhee as applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"districts, of a town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"city."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rope of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel's saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHl","text_ar":"رحل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is bound;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaAD","text_ar":"اَرْبَاض"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ropes of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that is next the ground thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the rope of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHl","text_ar":"رحل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) not what is above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHl","text_ar":"رحل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) accord. to Lth, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the belly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camel that is next the ground when he lies down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA; *) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belly of the she-camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner IAar explains the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaADN","text_ar":"اَرْبَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bellies of camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says that this is a mistake. (TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A girth of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niTaAq","text_ar":"نِطَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is put upon the flanks of the she-camel, so as to have the haunches behind it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on either side, having at its two ends two rings, to which are tied the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woven,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaited, thongs called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anosaAE","text_ar":"اَنْسَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHl","text_ar":"رحل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is bound with it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  Also (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSaAriyn","text_ar":"مَصَارِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the belly, that have a winding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coiled, form;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are in the belly of a sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folding intestines of beasts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHat, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guts, bowels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestines, into which the food passes from the stomach;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoEaA='N","text_ar":"اَمْعَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contents of the belly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSaAriyn","text_ar":"مَصَارِين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except the heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the lungs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that comprises the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAyaA","text_ar":"حَوَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winding, circling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coiled, guts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestines"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (IAar, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyDN","text_ar":"رَبِيضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marobiDN","text_ar":"مَرْبِضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marobaDN","text_ar":"مَرْبَضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, K, TA:) some describe the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaD","text_ar":"رَبَض"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below the navel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marobaD","text_ar":"مَرْبَض","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the navel and above the pubes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","A","S","K","ISk","IAar","Sgh","L","Mgh","Ks","Lth","AHat"]},{"entry_id":"n14491","headword_ar":"رُبُضٌ","root":"rbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Holding back, through indolence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubuDN Eani AlHaAjaAti","text_ar":"رُبُضٌ عَنِ الحَاجَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) in [some of] the copies of the K, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlHAjAt","text_ar":"عَلَى الحاجات"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asofaAri","text_ar":"الاَسْفَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) means (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not rise to perform needful affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeys:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not go forth to undertake them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaDN","text_ar":"رَبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["A","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}